An academic staff member recommended for appointment shall be sent an appointment letter setting forth the proposed conditions of employment. The Association shall receive copies of all appointment letters. The Faculty Association shall also be notified of any subsequent changes to the terms of employment. Such notice shall be given in a timely manner and before the new terms of employment have been implemented. This letter shall contain
the proposed rank and salary;
a statement that the appointment is governed by the terms of this Article in the collective agreement, with the URL of the agreement;
the conditions under which a candidate may become eligible for benefits and a description of the benefits that are available;
a start and end date for the appointment;
day(s) and time(s) of the class, including the start and end dates for classes and the date of the final exam (if applicable);
the maximum enrolment for the class;
any special requirements for grading or preparation;
information on how the appointee can access library, computer, and other privileges;
information on compensation should the course be cancelled (see Article AE);
if the offer is made less than 45 days before the start of the semester or if a response is required less than 7 days after the offer is received, information on the compensation outlined in Article AE;

Sessional Lecturers shall not perform work for the University prior to counter-signing their letter of appointment without additional compensation; examples of work that shall not be performed without a counter-signed letter of appointment without additional compensation includes but is not limited to:
submitting Textbook orders;
preparing syllabi, lecturers, or examination and evaluation questions;
appearing in student information systems as the instructor of record;
Working with grading committees as in 11.05.2.A.III.

In the event an offer is not made at least 45 days before the start of the semester, the successful candidate shall receive the following compensation in lieu of lost preparation time; this shall be in addition to the agreed upon compensation:
For an offer made between 45 and 21 days before the start of the semester, compensation equivalent to an additional 1/20 of the base stipend for the Sessional Lecturer's rank;
For an offer made between 21 and 7 days before the start of the semester, compensation equivalent to an additional 1/10 of the base stipend for the Sessional Lecturer's rank;
For an offer made between 7 days or less before the start of the semester, compensation equivalent to an additional 1/5 of the base stipend for the Sessional Lecturer's rank.

